Former Bafana Bafana and Kaizer Chiefs defender Siboniso Gaxa has signed to MTN champions Bidvest Wits.Gaxa comes into the team after spending years at the Amakhosi, although his tenure at the team ended badly with the player insisting he still has an existing contract with Amakhosi and was seeking compensation for his release.&#8220;Welcome to the family Gaxa and we look forward to you adding your defensive skills to the Clever Boys backline&#8221; Bidvest Wits.Siboniso Gaxa is the newest Clever Boy. Welcome to the family #NewSigning #TeamBVW pic.twitter.com/rWxget7on3 Bidvest Wits (@BidvestWits) November 28, 2016This will be the Kwa-Zulu Natal born players fourth team and third in the PSL, he left Mamelodi Sundowns in 2010 for Lierse SK in Belgium and returned in 2012 to play for Chiefs until he was transfer listed during the off season.The player has 52 caps for South Africa and will be looking to revive his career at the Clever Boys.The player has three league trophies to his name , he first won it with Supersport United in the 2007/2008 season, then with Kaizer Chiefs in the 2012/2013 and 2014/2015 campaigns